10.1016/j.jasrep.2018.10.028

LAYSUMM

TITLE

Registering and documenting the stratification of disruptions and restorations in historical edifices. The contribution of archaeoseismology in architecture

PARAGRAPH

The paper deals with the application of the archaeological methods to the structural analysis and the modern methodologies of the point clouds survey, with the purpose of creating a series of products, all used to highlight the building and mechanical history of the edifices and to the knowledge of the seismic history of the territory.

The historical center of Florence and, specifically, the church of San Remigio, has been chosen as a case study to illustrate the aforementioned methodology.